==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scops owl
<hw>Scops" owl`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[NL. <ets>scops</ets>, fr. Gr.
<?/ the little horned owl.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of
numerous species of small owls of the genus <gen>Scops</gen> having ear
tufts like those of the horned owls, especially the European scops owl
(<spn>Scops giu</spn>), and the American screech owl (<spn>Scops
asio</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

